            What's New at the GFRC?
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Analysis of New ARPA Spending Data
                    

                The Treasury Department just released new data on state and local American Rescue Plan spending. Here’s what we’re learning.
            









                            Whose Recovery? What ARPA Spending Tells Us
                    

                Amanda Kass, Philip Rocco, & Molly Clark discuss challenges confronting state and local governments in spending ARPA aid.
            









                            Water Rate Setting in Illinois
                    

                The GFRC’s Primer about water rate setting and water bills in Illinois.
            









                            New Research on Bond Issuer Audit Times
                    

                Analysis by Deborah A. Carroll and Richard A. Ciccarone on municipal bond issuers’ audit times.
            









                            New Research On Income Taxes
                    

                New analysis by David Merriman and co-authors finds that achieving a “fair” state income tax system is complicated.
            









                            Keeping Up with the Times
                    

                Deborah Carroll, Shayne Kavanagh & Chris Morrill discuss the need for for governments to rethink their revenue streams.
            












            The Government Finance Research Blog
          Heading link



 
Copy link



The Government Finance Research Center at UIC is a place for sharing. Academics, practitioners and others can rely on its blog for commentary and information about promising and not-so promising practices and much more.
The GFRC blog features a succession of posts short enough to be read by busy people and long enough to offer strong content. They’ll be written by well-known experts in the field.
Check out our latest posts below and click here to see all blog posts.







            The Government Finance Research Blog
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Financial Reporting with Workforce Shortages
                    

                by Dean Michael Mead, Partner, Carr, Riggs & Ingram, LLC, and formerly Assistant Director of Research and Technical Activities at the Governmental Accounting Standards Board
            












                            Procurement: Local Government Collaboration
                    

                By Stephen B. Gordon, lead coordinator of the Continuity of Supply Initiative (CoSI)
            












                            Revenue Forecasting in Unforecastable Times
                    

                By Katherine Barrett and Richard Greene, senior advisors to GFRC and principals of Barrett and Greene, Inc.
            

















            A Conversation With...
          Heading link



 
Copy link



The Government Finance Research Center works with researchers from a variety of backgrounds to analyze the role that public finance plays in our lives. In the interviews below, we talk with experts to dig deeper into pertinent topics and get their perspective on the past, present, and future of government finance.
See our latest conversation below:


      Chris Atkins, Vice President for Digital Government Transformation, SAP and formerly chief financial officer, Indiana
    










